                            <div class="content-list-component text">
                <p>In a snicker-worthy disclosure by President <a href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/topic/donald-trump">Donald Trump</a>&rsquo;s longtime personal physician, readers of&nbsp;<a href="https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/01/us/politics/trump-prostate-drug-hair-harold-bornstein.html" target="_blank">The New York Times</a>&nbsp;learned Thursday that the leader of the free world takes a small daily dose of the drug finasteride ―&nbsp;&nbsp;otherwise known as Propecia&nbsp;―&nbsp;which is used to treat male-pattern baldness.&nbsp;</p>
                                                        <!-- entry_paragraph_1_ad -->
    <div id="entry_paragraph_1" class="ad_spot entry-body--paragraph-ad">
                
    </div>
                                                                
<p>The revelation by Dr. Harold N. Bornstein that the president uses a prostate-related drug to grow scalp hair was not previously known publicly, according to the Times story, and appears to explain why Trump has a very low level of prostate specific antigen, or PSA, a marker sometimes used to diagnose prostate cancer. The newspaper said it had four telephone conversations with Bornstein, whose office is in Manhattan, about Trump&rsquo;s overall health.&nbsp;</p>
                                                        <!-- entry_paragraph_2_ad -->
    <div id="entry_paragraph_2" class="ad_spot entry-body--paragraph-ad">
                <div id="div-clmb-ctn-235791-1" style="float:left;min-height:2px;width:100%;" data-slot="235791" data-position="1" data-section="0" class="colombia"></div>
    </div>
                                                                
<p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="206" data-total-count="1809">Bornstein, 69, said he takes finasteride himself and credited it with helping maintain his own shoulder-length hair. &ldquo;[Trump] has all his hair,&rdquo; Bornstein said. &ldquo;I have all my hair.&rdquo;</p>
                                                        <!-- entry_paragraph_3_ad -->
    <div id="entry_paragraph_3" class="ad_spot entry-body--paragraph-ad">
                
    </div>
                                                                
<p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="206" data-total-count="1809">Bornstein, who said he hasn&rsquo;t seen Trump since his ascension to the presidency, first came on the public radar in December 2015, when he released a four-paragraph letter extolling Trump&rsquo;s health.</p>
                                                        <!-- entry_paragraph_4_ad -->
    <div id="entry_paragraph_4" class="ad_spot entry-body--paragraph-ad">
                <div style="display:table;margin:0 auto;padding:5px 0 15px;"><!-- TEMPLATE CODE -->
<div id="dfp_MID_300" class="dfp clearfix">
<script type="text/javascript">
    (function(){
        var dfpController = window.dfpController;

        var dfp_placement_slug = 'entry_paragraph_4';
        var dfp_slot_id = 'MID_300';
        var dfp_div_id = "dfp_" + dfp_slot_id;
        var dfp_div_el = document.getElementById(dfp_div_id);

        

        var dfp_prefix = '' || window.dfpPrefix;
        if (dfp_prefix === "") dfpController.console.error("DFP prefix is empty");
        dfp_prefix = dfp_prefix + "_" + dfp_slot_id;

        var execute_display_in_template = false;
        

        googletag.cmd.push(function(){
            var dfp_slot = googletag.defineSlot(dfp_prefix, dfpController.methods.getSizesByPlacementSlug(dfp_placement_slug), dfp_div_id).addService(googletag.pubads());

            if (execute_display_in_template) {
                googletag.cmd.push(function(){ googletag.display(dfp_div_id); });
            } else {
                dfpController.methods.registerDfpSlotDiv(dfp_div_id);
            }

            dfpController.methods.attachAdReloadEvent(dfp_div_el, dfp_slot);
            return;
        });

        return;
    })();
    </script>
</div>
<!-- TEMPLATE CODE ENDS --></div>
    </div>
                                                                
<p class="story-body-text story-content" data-para-count="457" data-total-count="3710">&ldquo;If elected, Mr. Trump, I can state unequivocally, will be the healthiest individual ever elected to the presidency,&rdquo; Bornstein wrote. Trump, 70, is also the oldest person ever elected to the presidency. Eight months after writing the letter, <a href="http://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/trump-doctor-wrote-health-letter-just-5-minutes-limo-waited-n638526" target="_blank">Bornstein said he dashed it off in five minutes while a Trump limousine waited </a>for him to finish.</p>
                                                                                                                                                
<div class="hummingbird">
<p>Of course, with the revelation that Trump is taking finasteride, many rushed to warn of possible side effects ― <a href="http://www.mensjournal.com/health-fitness/articles/should-president-donald-trump-be-taking-propecia-w464526" target="_blank">including mental confusion and permanent sexual dysfunction</a>.&nbsp;</p>
                                                        
<p>Punchlines aside, the safety of the drug has been challenged.&nbsp;</p>
                                                                                                                    
</div>
<article id="post-14407">
<section class="clearfix">
<p>&ldquo;The FDA-approved pill has been called into question, with emerging research and a slew of lawsuits suggesting that finasteride may be more dangerous than previously believed,&rdquo;&nbsp;<a href="http://www.mensjournal.com/health-fitness/articles/should-president-donald-trump-be-taking-propecia-w464526" target="_blank">reported Men&rsquo;s Journal</a>. &ldquo;Users report that its side effects &mdash; inability to orgasm, painful erections, chronic depression, insomnia, brain fog, and suicidal thoughts &mdash; can last long after patients stop taking the pill.&rdquo;</p>
                                                                                                                    
<aside class="inset-related-content inset-fullnoimage"></aside>
<p>Since 2011, <a href="http://www.mensjournal.com/health-fitness/health/are-hair-loss-drugs-safe-20150914" target="_blank">at least 1,245 lawsuits have been filed against Propecia&rsquo;s manufacturer, Merck</a>, alleging that the company didn&rsquo;t sufficiently warn users of sexual and cognitive side effects. Patients and physicians reportedly call the effects &ldquo;Post-Finasteride Syndrome&rdquo; because, they say, symptoms often persist after discontinuing the drug. The <a href="http://www.pfsfoundation.org/news/u-s-national-institutes-of-health-recognizes-post-finasteride-syndrome-2/" target="_blank">National Institutes of Health has added PFS</a> to its rare-diseases database. Merck told Men&rsquo;s Journal the the company &ldquo;stands behind the demonstrated safety and efficacy profile of Propecia.&rdquo;</p>
                                                                                                                    
<p>And of course, the disclosure about the president taking Propecia spurred many to ask: <a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2017/02/02/president-trump-appears-to-have-purposefully-hidden-his-use-of-a-hair-loss-drug/?utm_term=.40d7d79a5334" target="_blank">What other drugs does he take?</a>&nbsp;The Washington Post noted that <a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2017/02/02/president-trump-appears-to-have-purposefully-hidden-his-use-of-a-hair-loss-drug/?utm_term=.40d7d79a5334" target="_blank">Trump had multiple opportunities</a> to mention his Propecia use, but didn&rsquo;t.</p>
                                                                                                                    
</section>
</article>
            </div>
        
                
                
                
                
